property.configure:
An array of records that name an environment variable and a value:
{{name = "NAME1", value = "value1"}...}
Where NAME1 is the name of the environment variable, and value1 is the value. For example, {{name = "PTII", value = "c:/ptII"}} would set the value of the PTII to c:/ptII. If the parameter is set to {{name="", value = ""}}, then the environment from the parent process is used. If environmental variables are set with the parameter, the parent values may not be passed to the process. To view the current environment, use the "env" command.

